
[Paris, 5 Feb. 1785. Entry in SJL reads: Dr. Currie. Acknolege receipt his of Nov. 20.drop the scheme as to ground in Richmd. for a whilewar and peace doubtfulanimal magnetism dead, ridiculedif he should come here, invitation to bed and boardwrite by Fr. packet ut supra [entry follows that for TJ to Eppes, this date]. Not found. TJs decision to drop the Richmond scheme was evidently due to the arrival, on 26 Jan. 1785, of Eppes letter of 16 Sep. 1784 setting forth the necessity of settling all very urging claims and obliging TJ to think of contracting rather than expanding his Richmond holdings; see TJ to Eppes, this date.]
